business_proposition":true,"description":"If a worker gets accommodation as part of their job it can count towards the National Minimum Wage","language":"en","body":"\n<div class=\"summary\">\n<p>If an employer provides a worker with somewhere to live, it can be taken into account when calculating the minimum wage, up to a maximum of £4.82 a day or £33.74 a week.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>No other kind of benefit (eg food, a car, childcare vouchers etc) counts towards the minimum wage.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>What counts as accommodation charges</h2>\n\n<p>Include these charges when calculating accommodation costs:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>rent</li>\n  <li>charges for gas, electricity, furniture etc</li>\n  <li>laundry</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Working out if the employer provides the accommodation</h2>\n\n<p>The employer is counted as providing accommodation if any of these apply:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the accommodation comes with the job</li>\n  <li>the employer (or a connected person or company) owns or rents the property the worker lives in, even if there&rsquo;s no direct link between the job and the accommodation</li>\n  <li>the employer (or an owner, business partner, shareholder or director) receives a payment or benefit from the worker&rsquo;s landlord</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Accommodation costs count towards the minimum wage even if the worker doesn’t have to use the accommodation to do the job. If the accommodation is optional, it only counts as a cost if the worker uses it.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>Social housing providers</h3>\n\n<p>If someone working for a social housing provider gets accommodation from their work, this doesn&rsquo;t automatically count towards the minimum wage.</p>\n\n<p>It only counts if the accommodation is linked to the employment. For example, a care warden who has to live on site has their accommodation linked to their job.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>It doesn’t matter if the cost of the accommodation is taken from the workers’ wages beforehand or if the worker pays the cost after they’ve received their wages.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Higher or further education institutions</h2>\n\n<p>Accommodation isn&rsquo;t counted when working out the minimum wage if it&rsquo;s provided by a higher or further education institution to a worker who is enrolled on a full-time course with the institution.</p>\n\n<h2>Help and advice</h2>\n\n<p>If you have any queries about workers&rsquo; rights and the National Minimum Wage, call the <a href=\"/pay-and-work-rights-helpline\" title=\"Pay and Work Rights Helpline\">Pay and Work Rights Helpline</a>.</p>\n","alternative_title":""},"tags":[{"title":"Your pay, tax and the National Minimum Wage","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/working%2Ftax-minimum-wage.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes National Minimum Wage rates, keeping pay records and pay rights","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=working%2Ftax-minimum-wage","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/working/tax-minimum-wage"},"parent":{"title":"Working, jobs and pensions","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/working.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes holidays and finding a job","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=working","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/working"},"parent":null}},{"title":"Payroll","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people%2Fpayroll.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Paying HMRC, employee expenses and benefits and paying staff","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people%2Fpayroll","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people/payroll"},"parent":{"title":"Employing people","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-peo