yer in term-time then your Income Tax and National Insurance are usually taken automatically from your wages through Pay As You Earn (<abbr title=\"Pay As You Earn\">PAYE</abbr>).</p>\n\n<h2>Holiday jobs in the UK</h2>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re a full-time student with a holiday job, you may get your wages without tax being deducted. To do this you need to fill in a <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/students/work_hols_while_student_8_1.htm\" title=\"P38(S) form\">P38(S) form.</a></p>\n\n<p>The following also needs to apply:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re a full-time student in the UK only working in the holidays</li>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re returning to full-time education after the holiday</li>\n  <li>your total income for the year is below the Personal Allowance</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If you don&rsquo;t qualify for exemption you need to pay tax through <abbr title=\"Pay As You Earn\">PAYE</abbr>. </p>\n\n<p>You still need to pay <abbr title=\"National Insurance\">NI</abbr> if you earn more than the threshold.</p>\n\n<h2>Holiday jobs abroad</h2>\n\n<p>If you normally live and study in the UK but work abroad during the holidays you&rsquo;ll need to pay:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>UK tax on anything you earn above the Personal Allowance</li>\n  <li><abbr title=\"National Insurance\">NI</abbr> if you work for a UK employer</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If you work for a foreign employer you don&rsquo;t need to pay <abbr title=\"National Insurance\">NI</abbr> in the UK, but you might have to pay contributions in the country you&rsquo;re working in. </p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong><abbr title=\"Her Majesty's Revenue and Customs\">HMRC</abbr></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Telephone:</strong> 0845 300 0627<br />\n<strong>Textphone:</strong> 0845 302 1408<br />\nMonday to Friday, 8am to 8pm<br />\nSaturday, 8am to 4pm</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>If you&rsquo;re self-employed</h2>\n\n<p>If you work for yourself you need to fill in a Self Assessment tax return each tax year, with details of your income and expenses. <abbr title=\"Her Majesty's Revenue and Customs\">HMRC</abbr> then work out how much tax you need to pay.</p>\n\n<p>Find out more about <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/startingup\" title=\"becoming self-employed\">becoming self-employed.</a> </p>\n\n<h2>Foreign students working in the UK</h2>\n\n<p>If you work in the UK while studying you&rsquo;ll normally pay UK tax and <abbr title=\"National Insurance\">NI</abbr>.</p>\n\n<p>You may be able to reclaim this tax when you leave by filling in a <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/cnr/p85_p85s.htm\" title=\"P85 form.\">P85 form.</a></p>\n\n<h2>Overpaying tax</h2>\n\n<p>You can use <abbr title=\"Her Majesty's Revenue and Customs\">HMRC</abbr>&rsquo;s <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/calcs/stc.htm\" title=\"Tax checker\">tax checker</a> to find out if you might have paid too much tax.</p>\n\n<h2>Help</h2>\n\n<p>If you need help contact <abbr title=\"Her Majesty's Revenue and Customs\">HMRC</abbr> on 0845 300 0627. </p>\n\n","alternative_title":""},"tags":[{"title":"Your pay, tax and the National Minimum Wage","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/working%2Ftax-minimum-wage.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes National Minimum Wage rates, keeping pay records and pay rights","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=working%2Ftax-minimum-wage","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/working/tax-minimum-wage"},"parent":{"title":"Working, jobs and pensions","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/working.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes holidays and finding a job","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=working","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/working"},"parent":null}}],"related":[{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/national-minimum-wage-rates.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/national-