en from tips</li>\n  <li>what happens during leave (eg holidays, sick leave, parental leave)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Where to get help</h2>\n\n<p>If you have a question about tips or the National Minimum Wage, call the Pay and Work Rights Helpline:</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Pay and Work Rights Helpline</strong><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 0800 917 2368<br />\n<strong>Textphone:</strong> 0800 121 4042<br />\nMonday to Friday, 8am to 8pm<br />\nSaturday, 9am to 1pm</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Make an enquiry using the online Pay and Work Rights <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://payandworkrights.direct.gov.uk/\" title=\"Pay and Work Rights enquiry form\">general enquiry form</a></p>\n\n<p>Use the Pay and Work Rights <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://payandworkrights.direct.gov.uk/complaints/\" title=\"Pay and Work Rights complaints form\">complaints form.</a></p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/tips-at-work/tips-and-tax","slug":"tips-and-tax","order":2,"title":"Tips and tax","body":"<p>You have to pay <a href=\"/income-tax\" title=\"Income Tax\">Income Tax</a> on any tips you get, and sometimes <a href=\"/national-insurance\" title=\"National Insurance\">National Insurance</a> contributions as well. </p>\n\n<p>How your tax is worked out, and whether you have to pay National Insurance, depends on who:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the tips are given to</li>\n  <li>decides how the tips are shared out</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Cash tips paid directly to you</h2>\n\n<p>If you get cash tips directly from a customer, you have to pay tax on them but not National Insurance. </p>\n\n<p>If you fill in a <a href=\"/file-your-self-assessment-tax-return\" title=\"Self Assessment\">Self Assessment</a> tax return, you have to include the tips on it.</p>\n\n<p>If you don&rsquo;t fill out a tax return then HM Revenue &amp; Customs (<abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>) will estimate your tips based on information from you or your employer. <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> will give your employer a tax code so they can collect tax through Pay As You Earn (<abbr title=\"Pay As You Earn\">PAYE</abbr>). This is where tax is taken from your wages before you get them. </p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>If you think your tax code is wrong, <a href=\"http://search2.hmrc.gov.uk/kbroker/hmrc/contactus/search.ladv?sr=0&amp;as=1&amp;cs=ISO-8859-1&amp;sc=hmrc&amp;sf=&amp;sm=0&amp;nh=50&amp;ha=34&amp;tx0=49612&amp;fl0=__dsid:&amp;tx1=2037&amp;raction=view\" title=\"contact HMRC\" rel=\"external\">contact <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>.</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Tips included in card or cheque payments</h2>\n\n<p>If your employer pays these to you directly, they&rsquo;re responsible for making sure Income Tax is paid through <abbr title=\"Pay As You Earn\">PAYE</abbr>. </p>\n\n<p>Sometimes the tips are pooled together and shared out - this is called a &lsquo;tronc&rsquo;. The person who looks after it is called the &lsquo;troncmaster&rsquo; and they are responsible for making sure Income Tax is paid. </p>\n\n<p>If your employer decides how the tips are shared out, National Insurance is due as well as tax. Your employer is responsible for making sure it&rsquo;s paid through <abbr title=\"Pay As You Earn\">PAYE</abbr>. </p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Your employer has to tell <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> if there’s a tronc and who the troncmaster is.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re the troncmaster, you can get help on what to do from the <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/bst/advice-teams-area/map2.htm\" title=\"Business Education and Support Team\">Business Education and Support Team</a> in your area. There&rsquo;s also a leaflet to help you.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/helpsheets/e24.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Tips, Gratuities, Service Charges and Troncs' advice leaflet (PDF, 60KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Tips, Gratuities, Service Charges and Troncs’ advice leaflet (PDF, 60KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Service charges</h2>\n\n<p>These are added to the bill before it&rsquo;s given to the customer. </p>\n\n<p>If the charge is compulsory, it&rsquo;s not a tip so if your employer gives it to you, it&rsquo;s treated in the same way as your wages. </p>\n\n<p>If it&rsquo;s voluntary, you pay tax and National Insurance in the same way as for tips.</p>\n\n<h2>Bonuses</h2>\n\n<p>These are part of your pay and you&rsquo;ll pay tax and National Insurance on them through <abbr title=\"Pay As You Earn\">PAYE</abbr>. </p>\n\n"}]},"tags":[{"title":"Your pay, tax and the National Minimum Wage","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/working%2Ftax-minimum-wage.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes National Minimum Wage rates, keeping pay records and pay rights","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=working%2Ftax-minimum-wage","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/working/tax-minimum-wage"},"parent":{"title":"Working, jobs and pensions","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/working.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes holidays and finding a job","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=working","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/working"},"parent":null}}],"related":[{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/income-tax.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/income-tax","title":"Income Tax","format":"guide","updated_at":"2012-10-22T15:25:14+00:00"},{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/national-insurance.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/national-insurance","title":"National Insurance","format":"guide","updated_at":"2012-12-14T11:46:43+00:00"},{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/national-minimum-wage-rates.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/national-minimum-wage-rat