Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>). It regulates payments from contractors to subcontractors in the building industry. </p>\n\n<p>All building contractors and subcontractors should register with the scheme. </p>\n\n<h2>Who is a <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> contractor?</h2>\n\n<p>Anyone who uses subcontractors for construction work needs to <a href=\"/what-you-must-do-as-a-cis-contractor/register-with-cis\" title=\"register as a CIS contractor\">register as a <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> contractor</a> with <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>.</p>\n\n<h2>Who is a <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> subcontractor?</h2>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re self-employed and agree to do construction work for a contractor, you&rsquo;re a <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> subcontractor. You should <a href=\"/what-you-must-do-as-a-cis-subcontractor/register-with-cis\" title=\"register as a CIS subcontractor\">register with <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr></a>.</p>\n\n<p>Subcontractors can also be companies.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>If you’re a contractor and subcontractor, you must register as both.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Other people and organisations covered by <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr></h2>\n\n<p>Apart from builders, <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> can also apply to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>labour agencies and staff bureaux </li>\n  <li>gangmasters (or gang leaders)</li>\n  <li>property developers</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Even if your organisation doesn&rsquo;t do building work, you still have to register if you spend more than an average of £1 million a year on construction over a 3-year period. </p>\n\n<p>Organisations where this could apply include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>housing associations or &lsquo;arm&rsquo;s length&rsquo; management organisations (<abbr title=\"arm's length management organisations\">ALMOs</abbr>)</li>\n  <li>local authorities  </li>\n  <li>government departments</li>\n  <li>other public bodies</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>There&rsquo;s more information on who <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> applies to in the <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> guide for contractors and subcontractors.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/forms/cis340.pdf\" title=\"Download 'CIS guide for contractors and subcontractors' (PDF, 267KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘<abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> guide for contractors and subcontractors’ (PDF, 267KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/what-is-the-construction-industry-scheme/work-covered-by-cis","slug":"work-covered-by-cis","order":2,"title":"Work covered by CIS","body":"<p>As a general rule, the Construction Industry Scheme (<abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr>) includes almost any work that is done:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>to a permanent building</li>\n  <li>to a temporary structure (eg scaffolding)</li>\n  <li>in civil engineering (eg bridges)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Some of the types of work covered by the scheme include jobs like:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>site preparation</li>\n  <li>general construction - bricklaying, roofing, plastering and so on</li>\n  <li>alterations and extensions</li>\n  <li>repairs and refurbishment</li>\n  <li>decorating</li>\n  <li>dismantling work</li>\n  <li>demolition</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>There&rsquo;s a full list of types of construction work included and excluded from <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> in the <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> guide for contractors and subcontractors.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/forms/cis340.pdf\" title=\"Download 'CIS guide for contractors and subcontractors' (PDF, 267KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘<abbr title=\"Construct