don&rsquo;t have to have a certain number of subcontractors to use this system). </p>\n\n<p>There&rsquo;s more information about this on the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/cis/returns/edi.htm\" title=\"EDI filing for large contractors\"><abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> website.</a> </p>\n\n<h2>Pay your subcontractors</h2>\n\n<p>When you verify your subcontractors, <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> will tell you the right rate to deduct from any payments you make to them - or whether to pay them gross.</p>\n\n<p>You can pay your subcontractors directly or through a third party if they ask you to.</p>\n\n<p>If you make deductions from subcontractors&rsquo; payments, you must give them a payment and deduction statement.  </p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/forms/cis-payment-deduction-statement.pdf\" title=\"Download sample payment and deduction statement (PDF, 27KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download sample payment and deduction statement (PDF, 27KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/what-you-must-do-as-a-cis-contractor/pay-cis-deductions-to-hmrc","slug":"pay-cis-deductions-to-hmrc","order":3,"title":"Pay CIS deductions to HMRC","body":"<p>You must pay HM Revenue &amp; Customs (<abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>) any Construction Industry Scheme (<abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr>) deductions you make  from payments to your <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> subcontractors.  </p>\n\n<p>The standard rate of deduction is 20%, but there is also a higher rate of 30%. You&rsquo;ll take the higher rate from the earnings of some subcontractors - <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> will tell you when to do this.</p>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> will tell you:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>whether or not you need to make deductions </li>\n  <li>the rate you need to use </li>\n